name: estimated-potentiometric-surface-by-dagnese-and-others-1998-for-the-death-valley-regional-groun83a1f
notes: D'Agnese and others (1998) developed a potentiometric surface to conceptualize the regional ground-water flow system and to construct numerical flow models of the Death Valley region, Nevada and California. The estimated potentiometric surface was derived using a gridding algorithm and interactive editing to produce contours representative of the natural water-table conditions. Input data included the altitudes of lakes, springs, and wetlands; water-level data from wells; and hydrogeologic information pertaining to areas of recharge, discharge, and low- permeability rocks
